<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-19"><hi rend="italic">May 19,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hill replies in the negative to Mr. Powell’s request to be permitted
                            to take the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Topeka</hi> to St. Marc to
                            consult with the commander of the army of the north and advises him not
                            to go to Port au Prince, stating that there appears to be no occasion
                            for Mr. Powell’s intervention.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>